We managed to trigger an access violation in NumPy, coming from `_descriptor_from_pep3118_format` in `numpy/core/src/multiarray/buffer.c`.

The relevant lines are:

```
    if (descr == NULL) {
        PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
                     "'%s' is not a valid PEP 3118 buffer format string", buf);
        return NULL;
    }
```

Here `buf` refers to a buffer that was `malloc`ed earlier in the function; by the time we get to this line, `buf` has already been `free`d, so we get an access violation when building the exception message.

